<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
 Code Artifact: ic_launcher_round.xml
 Description: Defines the round adaptive launcher icon layers for Android launchers that request it.
 Programmer: HudLink development team (Brandon Dodge, Zach Sevart, Asa Maker, Jonathan Gott, Josh Dwoskin)
 Date Created: 2026-02-15
 Revision History:
 - 2026-02-15 - Zach Sevart - Added starter round launcher icon resource.
 - 2026-04-26 - HudLink development team - Added release prologue comments for sprint submission.
 Preconditions: Android API 26+ adaptive icon tooling reads this resource.
 Acceptable Inputs: Valid background color and foreground drawable resource references.
 Unacceptable Inputs: Missing drawable references, missing colors, or malformed adaptive-icon XML.
 Postconditions: Android launchers can render the round HUD-Link app icon.
 Return Values: Icon XML does not return values; Android generates mipmap resource IDs.
 Error and Exception Conditions: Resource compilation fails on invalid XML or unresolved resource references.
 Side Effects: Adds round launcher icon metadata to the generated APK.
 Invariants: The icon uses the same foreground mark as the square launcher icon.
 Known Faults: Artwork is placeholder-level and can be replaced by a final brand asset.
 Major Blocks: The background layer supplies color, and the foreground layer supplies the vector mark.
 Line Comments: XML comments are kept at the artifact level because the layer tags are standard Android icon syntax.
-->
<adaptive-icon xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android">
    <background android:drawable="@color/purple_500"/>
    <foreground android:drawable="@drawable/ic_launcher_foreground"/>
</adaptive-icon>
